ROSACEA üß¨‚Å£
‚Å£
Rosacea is a common, inflammatory skin condition which is characterised by persistent redness and flushing caused by dilated blood vessels. It mostly affects fair skin types, specifically on the face, around the nose, chin, cheeks and forehead.‚Å£
‚Å£
The causes are idiopathic, genetics, immune system, environmental surroundings and even certain skincare products and treatments can all play a part - and the severity can vary. Mild rosacea can produce redness that can be sensitive and sore and in extreme cases, bumps, sebum-filled spots or even swelling of the skin. ‚Å£
‚Å£
There is no cure but you can try to control the inflammation. Here‚Äôs how:‚Å£
‚Å£
üî¨ Avoid aggressive skincare or oily formulations. ‚Å£
‚Å£
üî¨ Cleanse and exfoliate gently.‚Å£
‚Å£
üî¨ Protect the skin with my Anti-Pollution Drops and Sun Drops. ‚Å£
‚Å£
üî¨ Avoid extreme temperatures. ‚Å£
‚Å£
üî¨ Eat a balanced, anti-inflammatory diet and avoid alcohol and coffee. ‚Å£
